## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-140">在下面的示例中，方法返回包含已识别的短语语义 SML 的字符串。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-140">In the following example, a method returns a string that contains the SML for the semantics of a recognized phrase.</span></span>  
  
```  
private string GetSemanticsSML(RecognizedPhrase result)  
{  
  if (result.Semantics.Count > 0)  
  {  
    return result.ConstructSmlFromSemantics().CreateNavigator().OuterXml;  
  }  
  else  
  {  
    return null;  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-161">语音识别语法可以包括的语义信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-161">A speech recognition grammar can include semantic information.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-162">当语音识别器生成此类语法的识别结果时，则的语义信息可能包括在识别结果中根据所语法和在识别器的输入的规则。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-162">When a speech recognizer generates a recognition result for such a grammar, the semantic information might be included in the recognition result, according to the rules of the grammar and the input to the recognizer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-163">有关的语义信息的详细信息，请参阅[了解语义结果](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2a9dbd8b-cf6d-42cd-bbb9-ca0b3e534005)和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey>和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue>类。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-163">For more information about semantic information, see [Understanding Semantic Results](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2a9dbd8b-cf6d-42cd-bbb9-ca0b3e534005) and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> classes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-164">下面的示例定义的方法，从已识别的短语中获取特定的语义信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-164">The following example defines a method that gets specific semantic information from a recognized phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-165">此方法返回时，它包含的语义的密钥或为 null 的值，如果不检索的值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-165">When this method returns, it contains the value for the semantic key, or null if the value was not retrieved.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-166">此方法只检查顶级项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-166">This method checks only for top-level keys.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0a94-167">由于的语义信息包含在树中的值，则必须通过返回的语义值访问较低级别密钥。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0a94-167">Since the semantic information is contained in a tree of values, lower-level keys must be accessed through the returned semantic value.</span></span>  
  
```  
static bool TryGetSemanticValue(  
      RecognizedPhrase phrase, string key, out SemanticValue value)  
{  
  value = null;  
  bool found = phrase.Semantics.ContainsKey(key);  
  if (found)  
  {  
    value = phrase.Semantics[key];  
  }  
  
  return found;  
}  
```
